cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image generation and image-to-image translation using deep learning. The use of perceptual similarity and human perception also suggests a focus on computer vision. The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and regularisation techniques. Additionally, the use of the Normalised Laplacian Pyramid Distance (NLPD) as a measure of perceptual similarity suggests a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of image quality metrics suggests a possible connection to Multimedia (cs.MM).
